statistics playground spires image hep hepnames institutions conferences experiments jobs videos hep statistics playground a place where statistics from and about the spires hep databases will be shared the purpose of this area is to share statistical data gathered from the spires databases usually this revolves around citation habits of hep authors but other items of possible interest may appear here the title playground was intentionally chosen to remind the reader that there are many caveats about the citation counts in spires the graphs and statistics presented here are meant to be amusing and interesting in nature but should be treated as such we take care to post accurate information but errors will happen in our analysis and the underlying data please take this into account when using this information feel free to reproduce or use the data listed here with proper attribution also feel free to let us know if there are errors you have found or questions that you would like to see answered please remember that this page is not our primary mission at spires and we will present only information that is easy to extract from the database and only as we have time to do so list of answered questions how many topcited papers are in the database ages of physicists at publication of top cited papers where particle physicists study symmetry sept 2005 large numbers of papers written about the ilc symmetry august 2005 topcited paper on extra dimensions symmetry june july 2005 neutrino citations symmetry may 2005 john ellis rod steiger and co authorship in hep symmetry apr 2005 growth of eprints symmetry mar 2005 astrophysics papers cited by other fields symmetry magazine feb 2005 kaluza klein citations symmetry magazine dec 2004 ever wonder what your department does experimental collaboration size symmetry magazine oct nov 2004 publication rate of eprints highly cited theory authors topcite olympics papers by others often using our data stats email us spires topcites recent